{"article_id":"5sFprXi8N4gor9Fd","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"President Trump said Wednesday","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"that the U.S. military will not accept transgender troops into its ranks","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"or allow them to serve in any capacity ,","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"reversing a policy","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"that began under the Obama administration","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"- and triggering intense criticism from lawmakers and civil libertarians .","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"In a series of morning tweets , Trump said","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"that ,","depth":12},{"id":9,"text":"after consulting `` with my generals and military experts ,","depth":13},{"id":10,"text":"'' the U.S. government `` will not accept or allow transgender individuals to serve in any capacity in the U.S . Military . ''","depth":13},{"id":11,"text":"The U.S. military ,","depth":13},{"id":12,"text":"he said ,","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"`` must be focused on decisive and overwhelming victory","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"and can not be burdened with the tremendous medical costs and disruption","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"that transgender in the military would entail . ''","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"Trump 's decision was made Tuesday ,","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"and he informed Defense Secretary Jim Mattis later in the day ,","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"White House press secretary Sarah Sanders told reporters Wednesday .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"The policy","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"allowing transgender troops to serve","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"was `` expensive and disruptive ''","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"and affected military readiness ,","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"Democrats disagreed .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"Rep. Adam Smith , D-Wash. , ranking member of the House Armed Services Committee , called Trump 's announcement `` an unwarranted and disgraceful attack on men and women","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"who have been bravely serving their country . ''","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"Chelsea Manning , progressive and LGBTQ groups slam President Trump 's transgender ban","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Accept transgender troops ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"allow them medical treatment ,","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"Adm. Mike Mullen tells Congress","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"It ' s unclear how Trump 's tweets will affect the estimated 6,000 transgender troops","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"who are already in the military .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Under the policy","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"announced in July 2016 ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"those troops were allowed to serve openly .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"Prior to that , the military discharged them for medical reasons .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"It 's also uncertain whether a series of tweets constitute a presidential directive ,","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"and whether Trump must sign documents","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"to make the new policy effective .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"After the tweets , the Pentagon issued a statement","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"saying only","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"that it would work with the White House `` to address the new guidance ''","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"provided by the president .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Brad Carson , the former chief of Pentagon personnel issues and an architect of the policy , said","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"Trump 's sudden announcement appeared to catch the Pentagon `` flat-footed , ''","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"and he predicted","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"the renewed ban will be challenged in court .","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"`` This will be devastating to those service members ,","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"but it will also hurt national security ,","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"as we have transgender people in many mission-critical occupations , ''","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"Carson told .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"Joshua Block , a lead attorney on the issue with the ACLU , said","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"the group most certainly will mount a legal challenge .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"But he noted","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"that Pentagon regulations","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"allowing transgender troops to serve openly","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"remain in effect .","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"`` Even the president ca n't eliminate regulations by tweet , ''","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"Block said .","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"The method of Trump 's notice by Twitter also drew ire .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Noting","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"that Trump 's statements are unclear ,","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"and that the Pentagon is already complying with parts of the Obama transgender policy ,","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"Sen. John McCain , R-Ariz. , said","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"the sudden news `` is yet another example of why major policy announcements should not be made via Twitter . ''","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"McCain , chairman of the Armed Services Committee , also noted","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"that many transgender troops are serving honorably","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"and that anybody","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"who meets medical and readiness standards","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"should be allowed in the military .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"Utah Sen. Orrin Hatch , R-Utah , issued a brief , pointed statement","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"criticizing Trump 's announcement ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"saying","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"discrimination in any form is wrong","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"and that he needs clarity from the military about what the tweeted policy means .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"`` Transgender people are people ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"and deserve the best","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"we can do for them , ''","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"Hatch said .","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"Meanwhile , former Obama administration officials , prominent Democrats and civil rights advocates condemned Trump 's announcement .","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"Ashton Carter ,","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"who instituted the policy","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"that would allow transgender troops to serve as President Obama 's defense secretary ,","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"the only thing","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"that matters","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"in choosing service members","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"is that they are qualified .","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"`` There are already transgender individuals","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"who are serving capably and honorably , ''","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"Carter said .","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"`` This action would also send the wrong signal to a younger generation","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"thinking about military service . ''","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"Former Vice President Joe Biden tweeted","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"that `` every patriotic American","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"who is qualified","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"to serve in our military","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"should be able to serve .","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"Full stop . ''","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"In a tweet of her own , House Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi , D-Calif. , told Trump","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"that `` this fight is not over , ''","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"and `` hatred will never defeat # pride . ''","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"The advocacy organization GLAAD called it `` another example of the Trump administration","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"attempting to make LGBTQ people invisible . ''","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"And some Democrats used the opportunity","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"to slam Trump 's own lack of military service .","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"In its statement , the Democratic Congressional Campaign Committee called the president a `` draft dodger . ''","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"Some Republicans also criticized the policy reversal .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"Rep. Ileana Ros-Lehtinen , R-Fla. , tweeted","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"that `` no American ,","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"no matter their sexual orientation or gender identity ,","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"should be prohibited from honor + privilege","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"of serving our nation # LGBT . ''","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"Many Republicans ,","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"including Vice President Mike Pence ,","depth":15},{"id":116,"text":"had criticized the transgender policy ,","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"and applauded Trump 's move .","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"Rep. Vicky Hartzler , R-Mo. , said on Twitter","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"that she was pleased to see","depth":16},{"id":120,"text":"that Trump `` shares my readiness and cost concerns , ''","depth":16},{"id":121,"text":"and `` will be changing this costly and damaging policy . ''","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"The issue ,","depth":15},{"id":123,"text":"she said ,","depth":15},{"id":124,"text":"comes down to military readiness .","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"She sponsored an amendment to the National Defense Authorization Act","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"that was narrowly defeated on July 13","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"that would have prohibited funding medical treatment for transgender troops .","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"However , the Pentagon commissioned a report last year by the non-partisan RAND Corp. on transgender troops","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"that found","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"medical treatment would cost no more than $ 8 million per year","depth":15},{"id":131,"text":"and have a negligible impact on the military ' s readiness","depth":16},{"id":132,"text":"to fight .","depth":16},{"id":133,"text":"Under Trump and Mattis , the Pentagon delayed implementation of a key portion of the Obama administration 's plan :","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"requiring the services to begin accepting and recruiting new officers and enlisted troops .","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"The Army , Air Force and Marine Corps requested more time","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"to implement the policy ,","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"saying","depth":15},{"id":138,"text":"they needed time","depth":16},{"id":139,"text":"to study the effects","depth":17},{"id":140,"text":"of accepting transgender troops .","depth":17},{"id":141,"text":"The Army has compulsory sensitivity training for soldiers and civilian employees .","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"Some members of Congress have also tried to limit spending on transgender troops in this year ' s legislation","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"authorizing military spending .","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"On Tuesday , in a statement to , former Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff , Adm. Mike Mullen urged the acceptance of transgender troops by the military ,","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"saying","depth":14},{"id":146,"text":"that previous policies","depth":16},{"id":147,"text":"that prevented gay and lesbian troops from serving","depth":16},{"id":148,"text":"damaged the military .","depth":15},{"id":149,"text":"During his six months in office , Trump has reversed a number of Obama policies , from environmental regulations to U.S. membership in the Paris climate change agreement .","depth":5},{"id":150,"text":"The transgender announcement is the latest example ,","depth":6},{"id":151,"text":"and it 's a decision","depth":7},{"id":152,"text":"that is likely to have political implications .","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"Trump sought the support of LGBT voters during last year 's election against Democratic nominee Hillary Clinton .","depth":6},{"id":154,"text":"In tweet","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"sent in June of 2016 ,","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"he told the LGBT community","depth":8},{"id":157,"text":"that `` I will fight for you","depth":8},{"id":158,"text":"while Hillary brings in more people","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"that will threaten your freedoms and beliefs . ''","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"Yet social conservatives applauded the decision .","depth":7},{"id":161,"text":"Tony Perkins , president of the Family Research Council , said","depth":8},{"id":162,"text":"that ,","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"`` as our nation faces serious national security threats ,","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"our troops shouldn ' t be forced to endure hours of transgender ' sensitivity ' classes and politically-correct distractions like this one . ''","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"Republican consultant Liz Mair , a Trump critic , said","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"the decision could help him politically with socially conservative voters .","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"`` Even though this decision is totally cynical","depth":10},{"id":168,"text":"and was not made properly","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"and is dubious on its merits ,","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"Trump could look semi-reasonable ,","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"given the response and existing perceptions . ''","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"With Trump struggling in public opinion polls ,","depth":9},{"id":173,"text":"Mair said","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"the decision `` wo n't improve his approval rating","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"but might actually help stop some bleeding . ''","depth":9},{"id":176,"text":"Army orders soldiers to undergo training","depth":4},{"id":177,"text":"to accept transgender troops","depth":4},{"id":178,"text":"Services required to report plans","depth":4},{"id":179,"text":"to accept new transgender troops","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":359,"left":0,"right":358,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":358,"left":354,"right":357,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":354,"left":327,"right":353,"relation":"joint"